her silver car Through the blue concave
invoke Old Midnight's sister Contemplation sage
the rolling planet's song , And tuneful turning spheres :
what awful forms Yonder appear ! sharp-eyed Philosophy
who blushes at each gazer's sight
Then Wisdom's hoary head , with crutch in hand
in choral caves , Serenely gay , nor sinking sailors' cries
lutes Grace the soft warbles of her honeyed voice
